<h2 id="marcoev-property">Marcoev Property</h2>

\[p(s_t+1|s_t,a_t) = p(s_t+1|h_t,a_t)\]

<ul>
  <li>Future is independent of past given present</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="computing-the-value-of-a-marcov-reward-process">Computing the Value of a Marcov Reward Process</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Generate a large number number of episodes</li>
  <li>Average returns</li>
  <li>Concentration inequalities bound how quickly average concentrates to expected value</li>
  <li>It doesn’t require marcov assumption</li>
</ul>

\[V(s) = R(s) + \gamma\sum_{s^`\in S}P(S^` | s) V(s^`)
V = R + \gamma PV\]

<ul>
  <li>in this case, we know P and R, so It would be</li>
  <li>$V = {(I-\gamma P)}^{-1} R$</li>
  <li>Equation in MRP</li>
</ul>

